    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - 2000, 4000, 8000 - DESCRIPTION - SPLASH SHIELDS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPLASH SHIELDS</title>
        <para>Splash shields are part of the fender extensions on the 4000 and 8000 series vehicles. The wheel well
            openings in the fender extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. This protects
            the lower front of the cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, it also keeps the step
            cleaner (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900227">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900227" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900227.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 27. 4000 and 8000 Series Fender Extension/Splash Shield</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SPLASH SHIELD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
